         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden, ¶ 12/4/69 ¶  ¶ As indicated by last overland mail, dear Dr Hooker, you will now receive by the Anglesey the rest of the Dicotyledoneae for Mr Bentham's use. ¶  ¶ They are in two...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.04.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, ff. 376-7.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/4/69</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As indicated by last overland mail, dear Dr Hooker, you will now receive by the Anglesey the rest of the <name key="Dicotyledoneae">Dicotyledoneae</name> for Mr Bentham's use.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>They are in two large boxes and all examined with especial care; and in their forward state of examination will render the work for Mr Bentham comparatively easy. I am anxious to see the Flora finished by my lifetime, and as my health continues frail, I am glad that I got so far, and wish now only that Mr Bentham may push also on the work.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the limited spare time left to me I now commence to work finally on <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name>, and hope to have done with them before the end of the year, so that the next may be devoted to the supplemental volume. Pray aid as far as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg> can in getting the <name key="Acotyledoneae">Acotyledoneae</name> done by your English friends. You must have large collections at Kew, and if not soon a commencement is made the cryptogamic volume<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Only vascular cryptogamic plants (ferns and their allies) were included in Bentham (1863-78), vol 7, pp. 670–781.</p>
               </note> will not be ready in time. <name key="Algae">Algae</name> and Ferns might be looked on as done. If <name key="Fungi">Fungi</name>, <name key="Lichen">Lichen</name>s, <name key="Lichenastra">Lichenastra</name> &amp; <name key="Musci">Musci</name> were anew worked up, as far as the English material goes, we would have a fair frame work for future researches.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prof Lindberg will have looked over my mosses during next winter. But it would be well to have the opinion of an independent English observer on these plants also, of which I sent to Kew very many. The <name key="Lichen">Lichen</name>s according to the new method need all careful revisal, and about <name key="Fungi">Fungi</name> is almost nothing extant, safe<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>save?</p>
               </note> the Tasmanian section;<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Berkeley (1860).</p>
               </note> so I hope Mr Berkeley will come to the rescue.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If we had once a good groundwork, I should more readily be able to work on them locally if I live. So do your best with Mr Benthams aid to set matters going.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller. </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
